{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/the-promise-of-alternative-data-in-finance-8b064d99d9a4", "time": 1682995779.291849, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/the-promise-of-alternative-data-in-finance-8b064d99d9a4/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "The Promise of Alternative Data in Finance | by Peter Went | Towards Data Science", "h1": "The Promise of Alternative Data in Finance", "description": "Because alternative data is transforming the investment management processes for asset managers \u2013 hedge funds, mutual funds, foundations, and pension funds \u2013 understanding the complex forces driving\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Correlating-S%26P-500-stocks-with-Twitter-data-Mao-Wei/1bd6a47c644454bb47c64c749f93a83804f8284a", "anchor_text": "researches correlated", "paragraph_index": 2}, {"url": "https://www.spglobal.com/marketintelligence/en/news-insights/research/natural-language-processing-part-i-primer", "anchor_text": "promise", "paragraph_index": 7}], "all_paragraphs": ["Because alternative data is transforming the investment management processes for asset managers \u2013 hedge funds, mutual funds, foundations, and pension funds \u2013 understanding the complex forces driving this digital transformation provide strategic opportunities. Investment managers that do not follow this seismic shift and update their investment processes are increasingly facing strategic risks and disintermediation: they may very well outmaneuvered by existing and new competitors who build their process around alternative data.", "Sophisticated investment managers are increasingly augmenting their decision making processes using alternative data sources from news and social media feeds, metadata from email, voice, and video communications, information from satellites and other geospatial information. Most asset managers see direct benefit from using this information to improve their alpha generating capacity to bolster the performance from structured time series and accounting information. Many fundamental investors that incorporate alternative data are called quantamental investors.", "Combining information extracted from twitter information with sophisticated analytical tools, has been proven to provide significant added return to investment managers; not only theoretically, but also practically. In 2012, researches correlated S&P 500 stocks with twitter data found that daily number of tweets is correlated with certain stock market indicators and that movements in closing prices can be predicted more accurately when including twitter data.", "In a series of articles, I explore promise of alternative data, by more specifically answering a few critical questions by combining academic research with pragmatic experience from investment managers.", "Before we begin exploring, a few definitions. Generally, alternative data in finance encompasses data used to extract insights from non-financial and non-traditional to improve alpha generation. These alternative data sets are generated through various digital and non-digital interactions, and can often be a result of \u201cbig data\u201d or financial transactions, sensors, mobile devices, satellites, public records, and the internet, or exhaust data.", "The definition of alpha generating capacity in investment management describes the excess return over the portfolio\u2019s or a strategy\u2019s return above a set benchmark, which may be a market or an index standard. Alpha is the active return reflecting the performance of the strategy or the skill of the manager and comes from \u201calpha\u201d (the Greek letter \u03b1). The term used to describe the return attributable to market performance or behavior, which is typically called \u201cbeta\u201d (the Greek letter \u03b2). A good manager has a lot of alpha.", "Effectively, alternative data promises, and seems to deliver, excess alpha for sophisticated investment managers through better quality information. In finance the holy grail has always been finding sources of true and superior information and thereby gaining the advantage. Alternative data is just a new manifestation of this quest.", "A good example is the promise held by sentiment analysis and Natural Language Programming: information extracted from speeches, tweets, blog posts, news stories, press releases, and presentations using advanced analytical techniques such as machine learning and cognitive computing allow the rapid processing of this information at an extremely fast rate providing easily quantifiable metrics.", "To understand how alpha can be generated using the results from the digital economy, the next article explores how alternative data streams and new sources of information are constantly generated.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Data science r\u014dnin. \u6d6a\u4eba I teach machines to learn and people to solve problems. Analytics, strategic leadership, machine learning, alternative data, and yoga."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F8b064d99d9a4&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fthe-promise-of-alternative-data-in-finance-8b064d99d9a4&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fthe-promise-of-alternative-data-in-finance-8b064d99d9a4&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}